      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
      "body" : "@Totalfrickinrockstarfrommars, elementData = new Object[elementData.length] brings us back to O(n), because the JVM always makes sure to set every element of a new array to null.  Still, I thought your original idea was excellent, and I don&#39;t mean to detract from it.  We need a clear(newInitialCapacity) method!!!"
